SA recorded more than 200  Covid-19 related deaths in the past 24 hours, taking the national death toll close to  23,000. There were also more than 8,300 new Covid-19 infections recorded in the same period. Health minister Dr Zweli Mkhize said that the 8,319 new infections surfaced during   44,074 tests — a positivity rate  just shy of 18.9%. Of the latest 205  Covid-19 related deaths, 96 were in the Eastern Cape. There were also 42 in the Western Cape, 20 each in Gauteng and KwaZulu-Natal, 15 in the Northern Cape, 10 in the Free State and two in Limpopo. This means there are now 22,952 confirmed deaths from the virus across SA. TimesLIVE